    <stitle>RECONDITIONING ROTORS - DESCRIPTION - ROTOR REPLACEMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="7">
        <title>ROTOR REPLACEMENT</title>
        <para>If the part number for a new rotor is not known, accurate measurements will have to be made to determine
            the proper type and size of brake rotor replacement required.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure the brake rotor being removed as follows to help determine the proper size brake
                rotor required as a replacement.
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Measure outside diameter of rotor, refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401804">Figure 4.
                        <xref refid="f0401804"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401804" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401804" filename="../figg04/G0401804.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4. Rotor Outside Diameter</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Measure width of braking surface of rotor, refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401805">Figure 5.
                        <xref refid="f0401805"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401805" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401805" filename="../figg04/G0401805.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5. Rotor Braking Surface Width</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Measure width of rotor between braking surfaces, refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401806">Figure 6.
                        <xref refid="f0401806"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401806" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401806" filename="../figg04/G0401806.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6. Rotor Width</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Measure bolt circle diameter of rotor, refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401807">Figure 7.
                        <xref refid="f0401807"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401807" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401807" filename="../figg04/G0401807.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7. Rotor Bolt Circle Diameter</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Count and measure diameter of bolt holes of rotor, refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401808">Figure 8.
                        <xref refid="f0401808"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401808" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401808" filename="../figg04/G0401808.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8. Bolt Hole Size and Quantity</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Measure total rotor width from inside braking surface to mounting surface of rotor,
                    refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401809">Figure 9.
                        <xref refid="f0401809"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401809" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401809" filename="../figg04/G0401809.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="300"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9. Overall Rotor Width</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Check identification stamped on outer edge on rotor, refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0401810">Figure 10.
                        <xref refid="f0401810"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f0401810" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0401810" filename="../figg04/G0401810.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="352px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10. Identification Stampings</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
